1
00:00:12,638 --> 00:00:14,073
More.

2
00:00:14,098 --> 00:00:16,075
Careful, sir.

3
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:17,660
Hot day like today,

4
00:00:17,685 --> 00:00:19,896
too much oil in the machine
can cause it to blow a gasket.

5
00:00:19,938 --> 00:00:21,206
Look, man.

6
00:00:21,230 --> 00:00:23,315
There are two kinds of men
in this world.

7
00:00:23,441 --> 00:00:25,359
Those who drink
and those who pour.

8
00:00:25,484 --> 00:00:28,320
Shut up and fill my
glass.

9
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:41,600
Hey, you two.

10
00:00:41,626 --> 00:00:43,602
I used to be just like you.

11
00:00:43,628 --> 00:00:44,979
Worked dirt for the man

12
00:00:45,004 --> 00:00:47,147
till my hands bled.

13
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:48,607
But no more.

14
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:50,818
Do you know why?

15
00:00:50,843 --> 00:00:52,277
Because I learned

16
00:00:52,303 --> 00:00:53,654
that a man can never

17
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:55,197
drink his fill

18
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:58,225
by waiting in line
for the tap.

19
00:00:58,350 --> 00:01:00,311
That's
it!

20
00:01:00,436 --> 00:01:03,022
Listen to him.
He can teach you
something!

21
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,583
Boss.

22
00:01:05,608 --> 00:01:08,319
Good to see you,
my friend.

23
00:01:08,444 --> 00:01:11,906
And to hear that great
speech of yours.

24
00:01:12,031 --> 00:01:14,492
You know, I never pegged you
for such a deep thinker.

25
00:01:16,744 --> 00:01:18,037
Such a philosopher,
right, Tortuguita?

26
00:01:20,164 --> 00:01:23,668
I keep thinking
I should write a book.

27
00:01:23,793 --> 00:01:25,544
I just need to learn
how to write.

28
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:35,446
So, what brings you

29
00:01:35,471 --> 00:01:37,598
to this burro's ass hole
of a town?

30
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:39,450
You'll see.

31
00:01:39,475 --> 00:01:40,993
Can we talk,

32
00:01:41,019 --> 00:01:44,104
or do you have
something to deliver?

33
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,748
Lots of time.

34
00:01:45,773 --> 00:01:47,833
Tortuga has his pace.

35
00:01:47,859 --> 00:01:49,318
Tortuga may be slow
out of the gate,

36
00:01:49,443 --> 00:01:51,445
but he always finishes
first.

37
00:01:53,656 --> 00:01:55,282
I like the way you
talk, Tortuga.

38
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:58,410
You've got
such a way with words.

39
00:01:58,536 --> 00:02:00,621
They just pour
out of your mouth.

40
00:02:03,082 --> 00:02:06,878
They flow like a
waterfall.

41
00:02:07,003 --> 00:02:09,421
But that's a talent,
isn't it?

42
00:02:09,547 --> 00:02:10,965
- You think so?
- He!

43
00:02:11,090 --> 00:02:13,901
Cheers to that!

44
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:22,101
Did you think I'd
forgotten

45
00:02:22,226 --> 00:02:23,853
- about your birthday?
- My birthday?

46
00:02:23,978 --> 00:02:26,330
Of course not, man.

47
00:02:26,355 --> 00:02:28,357
So bad I came all the way
here

48
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:29,775
to this burro's ass
hole

49
00:02:29,901 --> 00:02:31,402
to give you your
present.

50
00:02:31,527 --> 00:02:34,964
Present?

51
00:02:34,989 --> 00:02:36,908
No need to go
through the trouble.

52
00:02:37,033 --> 00:02:38,759
Forget it,

53
00:02:38,784 --> 00:02:40,845
I wanted to.

54
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:42,663
I have it for
you in the back.

55
00:02:45,083 --> 00:02:48,086
- Back there?
- Yes.

56
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:51,105
Come.

57
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:05,619
Follow me. Come.

58
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,955
look, look, look.

59
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:12,417
Is that my present?

60
00:03:12,443 --> 00:03:13,652
Yes, do you
like it?

61
00:03:13,778 --> 00:03:15,796
A pet.

62
00:03:17,907 --> 00:03:19,742
You won't be able
to take this one

63
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,702
to the park and throw
a ball for it.

64
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:24,080
It has the same pace
as you.

65
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:28,250
The pace of the turtle,
which is the best.

66
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:29,794
This is a very
special animal.

67
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:31,353
Why is that?

68
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,922
Imagine that its little
head

69
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:34,381
doesn't fit in its
shell.

70
00:03:34,506 --> 00:03:36,300
- It doesn't?
- No, look.

71
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:39,403
Look at it.

72
00:03:43,474 --> 00:03:46,310
Boss!
No, let me go!

73
00:03:46,435 --> 00:03:47,786
Let go, let me go!

74
00:03:47,812 --> 00:03:51,582
Boss!

75
00:03:51,607 --> 00:03:53,792
Boss, no, let me...!

76
00:04:29,187 --> 00:04:32,414
It's alive and kicking.

77
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:36,568
By the looks of him, he has
no idea how close he came.

78
00:04:36,694 --> 00:04:42,116
I'm assuming
Saul doesn't need to know.

79
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:44,051
Mum's the word.

80
00:04:44,076 --> 00:04:48,097
It never happened.

81
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:14,790
Son of a bitch!

82
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:28,095
Hi, Cielo, how are you?

83
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,513
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Walter,</font></i>

84
00:05:29,538 --> 00:05:30,998
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">What are you doing</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">in the house?</font></i>

85
00:05:31,123 --> 00:05:32,683
I'm back.

86
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:36,962
No, no, you're not
back,
get out of here!

87
00:05:37,088 --> 00:05:40,732
Cielo.

88
00:05:40,758 --> 00:05:43,302
Just come on inside
and we'll talk this through, ok?

89
00:05:43,427 --> 00:05:44,945
No!

90
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,305
I am not coming
in there

91
00:05:46,430 --> 00:05:48,615
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">until you get out.</font></i>

92
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,450
Look, this is also my house.

93
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:53,162
I have every right to be here.

94
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:55,606
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">But Walter,</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">we had an agreement.</font></i>

95
00:05:55,731 --> 00:06:00,627
an agreement I didn't accept.

96
00:05:55,731 --> 00:05:58,417
you made on your own,

97
00:06:00,652 --> 00:06:04,740
It takes two people
to make an agreement, Cielo.

98
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,117
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">But come,</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">why don't you come</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">in?</font></i>

99
00:06:06,242 --> 00:06:07,492
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Let's talk here</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">quietly.</font></i>

100
00:06:07,618 --> 00:06:09,178
No!

101
00:06:09,203 --> 00:06:11,663
No, there's nothing
to talk about!

102
00:06:11,789 --> 00:06:13,473
What I need is that you

103
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:16,518
get out of my sight now!

104
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:19,630
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">That's really what you</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">want?</font></i>

105
00:06:19,755 --> 00:06:23,734
Yes.

106
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:25,736
Walter, Walter!

107
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:45,964
What's the matter with you?

108
00:06:45,990 --> 00:06:47,425
What are you doing here?

109
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:49,243
I have every right to be
here.

110
00:06:49,368 --> 00:06:51,578
No, this is not your house
anymore.

111
00:06:51,703 --> 00:06:53,497
You don't live here anymore.
We're getting a divorce.

112
00:06:53,622 --> 00:06:54,915
I don't want a
divorce.

113
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,975
Well, that's not up to you!

114
00:06:57,001 --> 00:07:00,921
Cielo, this is all pretty
unfair, and you know it.

115
00:07:01,046 --> 00:07:03,048
Look, Walter, if you don't get
out of here right now

116
00:07:03,174 --> 00:07:05,843
I'll have to make
dramatic decisions.

117
00:07:05,968 --> 00:07:08,095
You kicked me out of
the house,

118
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:10,055
you're asking me
for a divorce,

119
00:07:10,181 --> 00:07:12,432
and now you're talking about
dramatic decisions?

120
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:14,326
I'm warning you!

121
00:07:14,352 --> 00:07:17,496
It could be worse for you.

122
00:07:17,521 --> 00:07:20,107
Anything that's worse for
me is worse for both of us.

123
00:07:20,232 --> 00:07:22,126
Please, be reasonable!

124
00:07:22,151 --> 00:07:23,919
No, I'm calling the police,

125
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:25,946
and I'm telling them
absolutely everything.

126
00:07:26,071 --> 00:07:28,048
There's the phone.

127
00:07:39,168 --> 00:07:42,187
It's ringing, they'll answer.

128
00:07:42,213 --> 00:07:44,022
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Bogota Emergency Line,</font></i>

129
00:07:44,048 --> 00:07:45,483
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">how can I help you?</font></i>

130
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:49,111
Yes, I'd like to report a...

131
00:07:49,136 --> 00:07:51,238
a domestic issue.

132
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:55,142
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">I'll put you through</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">to the Domestic Department.</font></i>

133
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:58,703
They're connecting me.

134
00:07:58,729 --> 00:08:02,566
Right hand to God,
I will tell them.

135
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:04,235
Do what you have
to do.

136
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:07,279
This family is
everything to me.

137
00:08:07,405 --> 00:08:09,698
Without it,
I have nothing to lose.

138
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,825
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Good afternoon,</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">this is Lieutenant</font></i>

139
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,952
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Armando Paredes,</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">of the Women Protection area.</font></i>

140
00:08:14,078 --> 00:08:16,372
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Tell me what your</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">current situation is.</font></i>

141
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:17,831
Thank you.
This is Cielo Restrepo.

142
00:08:17,956 --> 00:08:19,683
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Yes, how can I help you, ma'am?</font></i>

143
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,293
My soon-to-be ex-husband
broke into my house

144
00:08:21,419 --> 00:08:23,962
and I need an officer
to come and remove him.

145
00:08:24,088 --> 00:08:26,424
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">The system shows this address:</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">52 and 50.</font></i>

146
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:28,133
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">- Is that correct?</font></i>
- Yes, that's the address.

147
00:08:28,259 --> 00:08:29,968
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Yes, ma'am,</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">I will send the agents</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">right away.</font></i>

148
00:08:30,094 --> 00:08:32,096
- Okay, thank you.
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">- Have a nice day.</font></i>

149
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:41,897
Hey, dad!
How are you?

150
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:43,732
- I'm good, and you?
- Good!

151
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:45,984
Did you make up?
Are you back for good?

152
00:08:46,110 --> 00:08:47,794
Why are you home so soon?

153
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:49,254
Did you get out earlier?

154
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:53,925
No, I'm not early, mom.

155
00:08:53,951 --> 00:08:55,494
-How about a grilled cheese?
- Sure!

156
00:08:55,619 --> 00:08:57,721
Okay, you want one too?

157
00:08:57,746 --> 00:08:59,264
No.

158
00:08:59,290 --> 00:09:00,624
Go, go, Junior,
we'll catch you later.

159
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:03,168
Your dad and I have something
we need to discuss.

160
00:09:03,294 --> 00:09:04,769
Mom, can't it wait?

161
00:09:04,795 --> 00:09:06,838
I haven't seen Dad
in, like, forever.

162
00:09:06,964 --> 00:09:08,590
- Let's go, Dad.
- How is everything, okay?

163
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:10,134
- Yes, all good.
- Are you sure?

164
00:09:10,259 --> 00:09:13,053
- Are you behaving?
- Yes, yes, Dad.

165
00:09:29,278 --> 00:09:30,779
So are you gonna be
at work tomorrow?

166
00:09:30,904 --> 00:09:32,739
Yeah, that's the
plan.

167
00:09:46,545 --> 00:09:48,522
What's going on?

168
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:10,861
- Good afternoon, ma'am.
- Hi.

169
00:10:10,986 --> 00:10:12,837
Is this the Blanco residence?

170
00:10:12,863 --> 00:10:14,239
Yes, come
in.

171
00:10:14,365 --> 00:10:16,367
- Thank you.
- To the back, please.

172
00:10:16,492 --> 00:10:18,327
We were called
about a disturbance?

173
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:21,179
Yes, yes, that was me.

174
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,688
Good afternoon.

175
00:10:29,713 --> 00:10:32,857
You called the cops on Dad?

176
00:10:38,305 --> 00:10:40,599
I came home from work
and he was back.

177
00:10:40,724 --> 00:10:42,100
He had just moved back
into the house.

178
00:10:42,226 --> 00:10:44,478
And I asked him to leave,
but he won't listen.

179
00:10:44,603 --> 00:10:45,954
Well, there's a couple questions

180
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:47,456
I need to ask you, ma'am.

181
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:50,734
- Tell me.
- Did he strike you??

182
00:10:50,859 --> 00:10:52,377
No.

183
00:10:52,403 --> 00:10:53,878
Has he ever hit you?

184
00:10:53,904 --> 00:10:55,422
No.

185
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:57,924
This is not about violence.

186
00:10:57,949 --> 00:11:01,928
This is about trespassing.

187
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:06,333
I asked him to leave
but he wouldn't, that's it.

188
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:09,794
Let me get this straight.
You're divorced, then?

189
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:12,089
- Separated.
- Legally separated?

190
00:11:12,214 --> 00:11:14,007
There's not a court order,
if that's what you mean.

191
00:11:14,049 --> 00:11:15,675
But we've been living apart
for almost two weeks,

192
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:17,110
each on their own.

193
00:11:17,135 --> 00:11:20,780
I changed the locks.

194
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,240
Sorry, another question.

195
00:11:22,266 --> 00:11:26,645
Whose name is on the title
to the house?

196
00:11:26,770 --> 00:11:28,330
Both of us.

197
00:11:28,355 --> 00:11:31,108
But I need you
to please get him out of here!

198
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:33,918
Ma'am, we can't arrest a man

199
00:11:33,944 --> 00:11:36,280
just for breaking
into his own house.

200
00:11:36,405 --> 00:11:38,657
Not without a suit
or court order

201
00:11:38,782 --> 00:11:40,300
requiring he stays away.

202
00:11:40,325 --> 00:11:43,870
The baby!
No, calm down,
I'll handle this.

203
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:45,514
Please, I'm begging you!

204
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:47,791
Help me get this man
out of here!

205
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,586
Yes, ma'am,
but we need a reason to do that.

206
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,671
Are you sure
he hasn't threatened you

207
00:11:52,796 --> 00:11:54,314
or your children?

208
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:56,483
No. But having him in the house

209
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:58,302
is not a good thing.
Trust me.

210
00:11:58,427 --> 00:12:01,154
Officer.

211
00:12:01,179 --> 00:12:02,781
I'm aware that lately

212
00:12:02,806 --> 00:12:05,100
I haven't been
the best father in the world.

213
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:09,062
But you know, this happens
in every family.

214
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:11,081
Ma'am,

215
00:12:11,106 --> 00:12:13,609
is there anything
you'd like to tell us privately?

216
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,277
Would you like us
to have a word outside?

217
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:25,178
No.

218
00:12:25,203 --> 00:12:29,015
No, I'm fine right here.

219
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,559
I'm gonna level with you, ma'am.

220
00:12:30,584 --> 00:12:32,628
If you want him
out of the house,

221
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,813
you'll have to help me.

222
00:12:34,838 --> 00:12:36,856
Something to justify this.

223
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:39,551
Is it possible maybe he's broken
any laws or committed a crime

224
00:12:39,677 --> 00:12:43,763
that you know of?
Even if it's just a suspicion.

225
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:46,533
It's my mom's fault!

226
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:49,436
She won't even talk because
he didn't do anything.

227
00:12:49,561 --> 00:12:51,496
Mom's going crazy, dad!

228
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:52,814
Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey!

229
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:55,125
Junior, no, sir.

230
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:57,711
Son, it's not your mom's fault.

231
00:13:01,448 --> 00:13:03,341
No.

232
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:05,218
I don't know what to say.

233
00:13:07,329 --> 00:13:09,289
Well, that being the case,
there's no legal basis

234
00:13:09,331 --> 00:13:11,583
for us to remove your
husband from the house.

235
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:13,101
So if you'll excuse us,

236
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,378
we have other cases
to attend to.

237
00:13:14,503 --> 00:13:16,254
- Reyes.
- Thanks for coming.

238
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:17,715
At your service.
Let's go.

239
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:20,175
- Excuse me, sir.
- Please, I'm sorry.

240
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,593
No problem.
Excuse me.

241
00:13:24,888 --> 00:13:26,865
Okay.

242
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:28,325
Dad!

243
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:41,045
Ma'am, excuse me.

244
00:13:41,071 --> 00:13:43,407
If you still wish to provide
me any information,

245
00:13:43,532 --> 00:13:44,966
please call me.

246
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:46,826
- Thank you.
- Excuse me.

